trans-unit.source: FAQ
trans-unit.target: FAQ

trans-unit.source: What is a build concurrency?
trans-unit.target: What is a build concurrency?

trans-unit.source: A build concurrency is the number of builds that can run in parallel at any given time.
trans-unit.target: A build concurrency is the number of builds that can run in parallel at any given time.

trans-unit.source: When additional builds are triggered, they are queued and will wait for the previous one to complete.
trans-unit.target: When additional builds are triggered, they are queued and will wait for the previous one to complete.

trans-unit.source: What is a test device concurrency and a device hour?
trans-unit.target: What is a test device concurrency and a device hour?

trans-unit.source: A test device concurrency determines the number of devices you can use simultaneously.
trans-unit.target: A test device concurrency determines the number of devices you can use simultaneously.

trans-unit.source: For example, with 5 concurrent devices you can test 5 different device configurations in the same amount of time it would normally take to test 1.
trans-unit.target: For example, with 5 concurrent devices you can test 5 different device configurations in the same amount of time it would normally take to test 1.

trans-unit.source: We measure usage in device hours, which is a calculation of all activities on a device initiated by your test.
trans-unit.target: We measure usage in device hours, which is a calculation of all activities on a device initiated by your test.

trans-unit.source: For example, a 12–minute test suite run on 5 device configurations will consume 60 minutes, or 1 device hour.
trans-unit.target: For example, a 12–minute test suite run on 5 device configurations will consume 60 minutes, or 1 device hour.

trans-unit.source: Time spent downloading apps, processing screenshots, and generating test reports does not count as billable time.
trans-unit.target: Time spent downloading apps, processing screenshots, and generating test reports does not count as billable time.

trans-unit.source: What is included for free in push notifications?
trans-unit.target: What is included for free in push notifications?

trans-unit.source: Send an unlimited amount of push notifications to all your users at once for free with the ability to target 1000 devices per audience segment.
trans-unit.target: Send an unlimited amount of push notifications to all your users at once for free with the ability to target 1000 devices per audience segment.

trans-unit.source: How are monthly active devices calculated for push notification pricing?
trans-unit.target: How are monthly active devices calculated for push notification pricing?

trans-unit.source: When counting your app’s monthly active devices, an active device is defined by having the SDK integrated and launched the app at least once in the month.
trans-unit.target: When counting your app’s monthly active devices, an active device is defined by having the SDK integrated and launched the app at least once in the month.

trans-unit.source: What is included in the 30-day free Test trial?
trans-unit.target: What is included in the 30-day free Test trial?

trans-unit.source: For 30 days, you will be able to test your app on more than 450 device configurations.
trans-unit.target: For 30 days, you will be able to test your app on more than 450 device configurations.

trans-unit.source: With the trial, you can test your app on 1 test device concurrency with unlimited device hours.
trans-unit.target: With the trial, you can test your app on 1 test device concurrency with unlimited device hours.
